Title: Gham Ghi Island
Description: Visit Gham Ghi Island where you can snorkel and enjoy beach time

Title: Buom Island, Fingernail Island
Description: Visit Buom Island or Fingernail Island where you can snorkel

Title: May Rut Trong island
Description: Visit May Rut Trong island for lunch

Title: Seawalker
Description: Experience Seawalker (at own expense)

Title: Drop-off
Description: Drop-off

Title: End.
Description: End of tour.

Title: Flight check-in
Description: 20:40-08:00 Participants will be picked up by tour leader at Departure Gate at Tan Son Nhat International Airport for flight check-in. Overnight on the airplane.

Title: Arrival, start day 2
Description: 06:30-21:00 Arrival (Lunch/Dinner)

Title: Oshino Hakkai Ancient Village
Description: Oshino Hakkai Ancient Village—an ancient village located peacefully at the foot of Mount Fuji. To this day, the houses in Oshino Hakkai village still have ancient Japanese traditional architecture.

Title: Lake Yamanaka
Description: Swan Cruise experience on Lake Yamanaka (25 minutes).

Title: Mount Fuji
Description: Mount Fuji—the highest mountain in Japan at 3776 meters above sea level. Participants might board the 5th stop at an altitude of 2,300m for a better view of Mount Fuji (if the weather permits).

Title: Return to Hotel
Description: Return to Shinko Hotel (or equivalent) to check in.

Title: Experience onsen bathing
Description: Experience onsen bathing—a unique culture in the land of cherry blossoms.

Title: Start day 3
Description: 06:30-21:00 (Breakfast/Lunch/Dinner)

Title: Seasonal fruit picking.
Description: Seasonal fruit picking.

Title: Imperial Palace
Description: Imperial Palace—where the Emperor lives and works (visit and take pictures outside).

Title: Asakusa Kannon Temple
Description: Ancient Asakusa Kannon Temple—a sacred temple and one of Tokyo's oldest today with distinctive traditional architecture.

Title: Nakamise shopping street
Description: Visit the Nakamise shopping street in front of the temple.

Title: Tokyo Sky Tree
Description: Tokyo Sky Tree—Japanese TV tower, 634 m high and made of steel (visit and take pictures outside).

Title: Akihabara Electronic City
Description: Shop at the famous commercial district in Tokyo: Akihabara Electronic City where visitors will find hundreds of electronic items on display. The price of electronics here is 20–30% cheaper, there is also a tax-free priority for foreigners.

Title: Return to hotel
Description: Return to Shinjuku Washington (or equivalent) to check in and rest for the night.

Title: Start day 4
Description: 06:30-21:00 (Breakfast/Lunch/Dinner)

Title: Hitachi Seaside Park
Description: Hitachi Seaside Park with an area of about 190 Hectare is a place to see the unique flowers in Japan and is especially famous for the Kochia red grass every October.

Title: Visit Ushiku Buddha
Description: Visit Ushiku Buddha. In 1996, Ushiku Daibutsu was recognized as the world's largest bronze Buddha statue, inscribed in the Guinness Book of Records, and one of the wonders of the world.

Title: Ami Premium Outlets
Description: Continue sightseeing and shopping at Ami Premium Outlets—Japan's premier shopping district, boasting many of the nation's upscale stores.

Title: Day 5.
Description: 06:00-13:00 (Breakfast)

Title: End of tour.
Description: Transfer to the airport to fly back to Ho Chi Minh City. End of tour.
